The operation projected the subscription of 59.5 million euros from the company's 85% capital, which could expand next year to include the remaining 15%.
The aim of the purchase was to provide more value-added services to customers with the possibility of access to a huge international market.
This valuation and purchase and sale service is exclusively guaranteed to professionals in the sector, such as insurance companies, experts, rental companies, services, spare parts sales and professional dealers who must register before the start of operations.
This platform was established in 1996 in Germany and manages more than 650,000 operations across Europe, including 500,000 in Germany.
Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey stand out among the main markets.
The website currently has more than 1,500 registered vendors and 4,000 experts.
It manages 3,000 daily adverts, and about 100 new adverts are added to the Spanish market every day.
Under Spanish law, a car whose chassis number has been decommissioned cannot be returned to service, but can be used as a source of spare parts that have not been damaged.
Historical vehicles may have traffic permitted, although they were decommissioned, after preliminary driving.
Service budget in four steps
With the Auda-Taller, Audatex guarantees that the user only gets a budget in four steps: vehicle identification, spare part search, budget and budget generation
Ease of use is an essential condition for these systems, especially for the belief of older professionals, who to a greater or lesser extent are restrained in the use of new management techniques.
The database contains 1,034 vehicles, including 666 tourist vehicles, 109 off-road, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Naturally for use, you need a computer with an internet connection.
After identifying the model to be repaired, using the chassis number, a real graphical display of the model appears and then the necessary spare part is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price of the workforce, surcharges or discounts, and then print and hand over to the customer.
AudaTaller is not a valuation tool like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that it is service-oriented and does not include a workforce estimate.
The cost of using this tool for the workshop is 350 euros a year, which the customer can finance.
Currently, Audatex is working to make these views three-dimensional.
This is an innovation that mechanics welcome because, for example, it will allow you to select a door and turn it to show the inside.
